pan class=title> Re: !@</span><hr size=1> Vox is scheduled for the 19th and the 20th and we were gonna try on the 18th. Now even if we dont do it on the 18th the ones on the 19th and 20th may have problems.<br><br>Just want to get this cleared up. I will try and talk to the other guilds that were gonna try though one of them was a closed raid. <p>Troy Daedagor <BR> 55 Levels of Almost Always Having a Heal Memed <BR> <a href="http://www.gloriousrising.com"><img src="http://www.gloriousrising.com/forum_pics/signature_officer.jpg" width="200" height="45" border="0"></a><BR>   I'm a Templar?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usyniqueinlecebrae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Synique Inlecebrae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/11/01 1:14:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=743.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: !@</span><hr size=1> IMO anything with a multiple day spawn time should still be reservable, unless it is required to be dead in order for something to spawn for an epic.  i.e. Nagafen and Ragefire.<br><br>That includes dragons like Vox, Sev, Talendor, etc.  Sorry, I used to play in Mithaniel Marr, and this is how it ended up going totally FFA.... and there's a lot of unhappy people on Mith Marr if they aren't in a massive guild.<br><br>When I say reservable, I mean reserving that SPAWN of the NPC in question.  Not reserving that day.  Basically back to the way the calendar used to be.... if you have a Vox reservation for Saturday, and she pops on Wednesday or Thursday, that means nobody touches her until you've taken your shot at her on Saturday.  Making NPCs like that go FFA really favors no one but major guilds or people who are willing to drag half the server population to come help them.<br><br> <p><br><a href="http://www.titansofluclin.com"><img src="http://members.aol.com/synique/synsig.gif" width="500" height="100" " border="0"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utroydaedagor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Troy Daedagor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/11/01 1:36:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=743.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: !@</span><hr size=1> The problem with reserving Vox and Naggy has been looked at and determined that it is not a problem to kill them as soon as you can. Both are both Epic Related. In the case of Vox she needs to die as often as possible to have as many chances as possible for people to collect her very rare epic items. Naggy already gets busted very soon after he pops due to Clerics needing him dead. It has not been an issue to my knowledge and infact many people get to attend these raids. The change to a Lvl 52 limit really keeps the uber guilds from killing them all the time. The only real drawback is not being able to plan a Vox or Naggy raid in advance however there are plenty of times that Vox is up and no one is killing. <p>Troy Daedagor <BR> 55 Levels of Almost Always Having a Heal Memed <BR> <a href="http://www.gloriousrising.com"><img src="http://www.gloriousrising.com/forum_pics/signature_officer.jpg" width="200" height="45" border="0"></a><BR>   I'm a Templar?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uuladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uladar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=13173192&img=5 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eater of PoC CoRNz </span><br>  Posts: 198<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/11/01 11:04:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=743.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: !@</span><hr size=1> I 100% disagree with Synique.  Lets use Venril Sathir in our example here.  Venril Sathir is a 3 day spawn.  Your reservation is a wednesday.  Venril Sathir spawns on a Tuesday.  EVERYONE wants to kill Venril Sathir.  Lets say we are a huggly server where there is peace and joy and Chakan dances in fields of flowers with Large.  Your reservation gets honored and no one touches him.  Now Tuesday night there is an emergency patch to fix the problem where the Monk epic can be obtained by a level 3 by combining a fire beetle eye in the oven.  Oh crap, we just wasted a spawn for a NPC that would have been taken out a few hours within his spawn time.  But no, your reservation just wasted a spawn.  Venril Sathir can be taken down in a grand total of 30 mins.  If you cannot organize a raid on a weekday that will take at most one hour of people's time, then you should not be putting a rare spawn on the calender.  <br><br>Now lets move this to Vox.  Vox is only killable by groups of people that are not greater than level 52.  Because of this level restriction there is ZERO competition for said mob.  I would be shocked all to hell if Vox was dropped more than 3 times a month.  Therefore why put something on the calender that maybe 2 groups tops would be competing for.  Can't you just talk to them and work something out?<br><br>Now lets talk about the Dain.  Currently only LoS has been successful on killing the Dain.  I personally feel that no other guild is ready for an attempt at this time.  Endorean was ready, but after our reorganization we are a little down from our highest point.  There will become a time when we are ready to drop the Dain.  I know that once the time comes we are ready we will work something out with LoS.<br><br>All the calender does for rare spawns is waste spawns, and waste people's time.  We know what group of people are killing any given mob.  Why is it so hard to talk to those groups of people?  The calender is not the end all system that is going to have us holding hands dancing around the may pole people.  It is great for its given purpose.  Letting the 100 other groups that are capable of doing planes raids know that you are going to be in that given plane for that day.<br><br>That is all. <p><font color="green" size=+1 face="Arial">Outrider Uladar</a></Font><BR><font size=-1 face="Comic Sans MS" color="Navy"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucayleustarshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cayleu Starshine</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/11/01 11:21:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=743.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: !@</span><hr size=1> For the exact reasons posted above, things like Dragons, VS, etc should not be on the calander. A few things will have an orderly rotation which is private among those few guilds able to do the kill, but aside from that, if you reserve something for saturday, and it pops thursday, if no one cares about it, fine life goes on. If it is a highly-competitive creature like Nagafen, you have got to move your raid up. Even if a patch didnt happen to waste a spawn, if you string together 3 or 4 of these 1-2 day delays, there's your wasted spawn right there.<br><br>If you want to do a raid where youll be able to set a date and raid on that day regardless of what happens, then pick a less-desired target like Vox, and if someone else expresses an interest in also killing Vox (for example), work it out with them. If your target is something highly-desired where the server doesnt want wasted spawns like Nagafen, you should go in realizing that you will probably need to be capable of moving your raid up if you have to.<br><br>Anyway, of bish's suggestions, I would only add Chardok Royals for now, and perhaps ToV/VP someday in the future. (though a private arrangement/agreement among guilds will probably work better for this, since I do not forsee massive competition for those places) The Chardok Royals is not sharable, there is a higher than normal desire to raid this place, it's a big all-evening affair, and it does not depend on a wierd weeklong or 3-day random spawn. That's pretty much a definition of why planes are reserved. <p>Cayleu Starshine<br><font color = blue>Healer of Tunare</font><br><font color=red>Insidious Blood</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uveladorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veladorn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 498<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/14/01 6:52:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=743.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://yourpage.blazenet.net/anabelle/triad/valasclose2.jpg width=150 hieght=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: !@</span><hr size=1> Bish, is there anyway you can force people to enter either a guild name or open?  More and more I look on the calandar and I see it say PoF - Joe.  This seems almost meaningless.  Unless you know what guild Joe is in, its hard to see who is wher