hat has a long spawn time should be able to be reserved.  However I also acknowledge the epic issue.  If a mob spawns early then the person (or guild in his/her absense) should be notified and they NEED to organize a raid to take down that mob asap!  To say that spawns like Nagafen and Vox cannot be reserved is ABSURD!  If DOES favor larger guilds that can put together a raid on a moments notice.  Sorry, but everyone is entitled to dragon loot and epic pieces.  However if people start saying, &quot;Hey Naggy's up... let's kill him&quot; without any respect to the people organizing raids... it would be completely unfair.  It seems to me that too many higher level people and larger guilds are ignoring the fact that level 1 characters and guilds with 10 people in them still all pay the same $10 a month, and are entitled to the same opportunities.  Seems like everyone is overly worried about their loot and not about keeping the respect between everyone on the server.<br><br>I do agree however, that if special spawns are up for a respectable time without the scheduled party coming to kill them, then they should be taken down by the first person/guild able to do so.<br><br>Just my opinion, and I'm sure some will disagree <p>Nyatese Nivaro<BR>52 Wanderer of Luclin<BR>The Stryngs of Ayre<BR><BR>Cauldarin<BR>21 Cleric of Tunare<BR>The Stryngs of Ayre<BR><BR>Master Brewer (130), Baker (135), and Potter (131)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubishoopugget.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bishoopugget</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=57685510&img=5 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 405<br> <font color=#FF000