ker<br>Fellowship of Luclin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uungarraventhorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ungar Raventhorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 257<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/15/01 11:34:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=743.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A suggestion</span><hr size=1> Putting any 7 day on the calendar even on Wed doesn't work.<br><br>A couple weeks ago Verant unleashed patch hell on all the servers.<br><br>Just look at Venril Sathir.<br><br>Patch - VS killed by Triad<br>1 Hour Later - BOOM Emergency Patch - VS killed by LoS<br>Next Night - BAM Server goes down again - VS taken out again<br>Next Morning - ROFL Server Patch - VS does another dance <br>with death..<br><br>If add in two random patches a month that is enough to mess up any type of Monthly weekly reservation for a 7 day spawn.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uranmashinji.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranmashinji</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=61737088&img=5 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/16/01 10:03:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=743.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A suggestion</span><hr size=1> Naggy and Vox are still big bosses and when you get 3 groups all wanting to take him/her down at the same time what are you going to do?? Put him BACK on the calendar, so people can reserve him like always. You really don't want to change way when people are set in them... This is a BAD idea...<br><br>And if there is a &quot;list&quot; where is this list?<br><br>Ryochan <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uranmashinji.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranmashinji</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=61737088&img=5 BORDER=0> at: 5/16/01 10:07:27 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uteeil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teeil</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=EQ000530... BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/16/01 10:33:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=743.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://freeload.homestead.com/_ksi0701961584557075/skyscreamer1/files/EQ000530.bmp_ WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A suggestion</span><hr size=1> IMO making Nagafen/Vox FFA would be a terrible idea.  The reservation system has worked great for a long time.  People were patient about the dragon spawns, and raids were always efficient and done with cooperation with other players on the server.<br><br>However you make Naggy/Vox FFA you will make this server filled with people who will step on each others toes to do their epics.  They are rare spawns, they shouldn't be contested with by other players.  Its not fair to those (Sharia for example) who have been trying to get their books for months, and other players who are ready to attempt to go for them and the scales for the bard/warrior epics.  It makes me feel like there are some people on this server who are getting greedy and cant wait a week or two for their shot at the dragons.  <br><br>Look at clerics?  How long is the wait for Ragefire?  Three months?  I havent even SIGNED up for the list yet, just in case my turn comes up and I am not to that part of the quest for the cleric epic yet.  It wouldnt be fair to the guy or gal behind me who IS ready to do that part of the quest.  I dont plan on getting my epic til at least this fall, probably later.  Epic quests are supposed to take a long time, they cant be done in a week, or a month.<br><br>As for Nagafens loot...yes it is nice.  I agree there, but think about it...lots of warriors out there can live without the CoF.  Many do.  All his loot is very nice, and everyone who pays 10$ a month to play EQ should get a shotat it when they sign up for a dragon raid.  Doing this means that some guilds will have the power to basically farm Naggy and Vox and will create a glass wall for some people on this server who want to do their epics or get a shot at some nice items.<br><br>So, yes I am against making the dragons FFA.  Its only going to cause all the players on this server hardship.  Some people seem to think only of themselves though.  Please be considerate of other players, and keep the reservation system alive.<br><br> <p>Teeil De'Tharios <Br>High Vicar of the 52nd Season <Br>Duo Guildmaster of The Stryngs of Ayre <Br>Beloved Husband to the Lady Ezukara De'Tharios<Br><Br><img src=http://skyscreamer1.homestead.com/files/teeil.gif> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usenaiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senaiel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/16/01 4:10:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=743.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> This Dragon stuff</span><hr size=1> Hi I think not posting dragons on the calender is a horrible idea.  Me and Sharia get the job done for Vox i dont bother with Naggy anymore but in all cases it should still be on the calender!  I've been working on my books since God knows when now and all i need for FA is vox book. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarestarbladesinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FlarestarBladesinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/16/01 10:03:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=743.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This Dragon stuff</span><hr size=1> I've never been in favor of the dragons going FFA.... any of them.  Vox, Naggy, Gore, etc, doesn't matter.<br><br>Yeah, killing them faster means more will pop.  But put bluntly, that also denies as many people their chance at what they need as it does opens up for others.  That's great, dragon dies every Wednesday for four months straight.  Some people have work in the morning, and CAN'T stay up like that, hence the concept of weekend raids.<br><br>I'm not one of those.  I own my own business, can generally stay up as long as I like.  But I still don't like the idea of doing something like this.  One of my main servers used to be Mithaniel Marr.  Mith Marr at one point had a reservation system of sorts.  It was a very pleasant server to be on at that time.  Mith Marr is also now totally FFA.  It's not a server worth playing on unless you join an uberguild, if you have any aspirations towards an epic that has a contended spawn.  The uberguilds have hordes of twinks that kill Vox and Nagafen most pops, and the other dragons are killed upon popping, generally.  Veeshan is in the same boat, as are several other servers.<br><br>So will making the dragons go FFA really mean that many fewer dragon kills?  Not really, no.  Patches have been far in-between lately, and with Shadows of Luclin coming out I'd say they'll stay that way.  Let the reservation system stand as it was.<br><br>Flarestar Bladesinger <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubishoopugget.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bishoopugget</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=57685510&img=5 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/17/01 12:42:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=743.topic&index=21>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://everquest.estoncom.com/images/bishnut.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This Dragon stuff</span><hr size=1> Please read this carefully.<br><br>This is not about Dragons becoming FFA.  This has nothing to do with FFA.<br><br>This has to do with the following question.  Does the calendar serve its intended purpose when it comes to 7 day spawns?<br><br>Tell me, when you post a &quot;reservation&quot; on the calendar for a dragon, does that do *anything* to ensure that you will get to attempt that dragon that day?  No, absolutely nothing.  In fact, there's approximately a 14% chance that the dragon will even be there if the dragons are killed on a regular basis and you aren't lucky enough to post on a patch day.<br><br>When you use a list to reserve long spawn time mobs, when you are on the top of the list you get the next spawn, very simple.  No more posting 15 times over two months to try to make sure you get at least a couple dragon kills.<br><br>Please, don't convince me what the calendar does and doesn't do, I created the thing in the first place.<br><br>4 Vox reservations in one week?  WHY???  She only spawns once (barring patches) a week!<br><br>Where's the list?  I don't know, why doesn't someone make one?  Am I supposed to make it even though I have little desire to raid old world dragons?  Many months ago I thought that a graphical calendar would be much easier to read than the clutter on the dragons and planes board.  You know what I did?  I made a calendar, showed it around, got some support, and most people started using it.<br><br>If you can give me a simple, straight forward reason as to why throwing darts at the calendar and hoping to pick the right day a dragon is up is better than using list reservation for the dragons, sure, I will reopen the discussion about whether they belong on the calendar.  A discussion, by the way, that the majority of us had many months ago and came to a agreement that, at the time, was uncontested.<br><br>I apologize for being grumpy, but it seems that I'm getting arguements on things that don't really have to do with the subject or am being contradicted by people that either haven't read everything I've written or haven't researched any of the discussions we've had about these subjects for the last year.<br><br>I run a calendar for all of you that I don't even use.  I run it out of respect for this server and for my friends.  I would wholly appreciate the respect of fully reading what I'm saying before arguing and making points that have little to nothing to do with the current proposal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showMessageRange?topicID=743.topic&start=21&stop=36>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335drago